Урок по PowerShell: никогда не использовать Get-Content + Set-Content без -Encoding UTF8 для файлов с кириллицей или emoji — PS5 на русской Windows использует CP-1251 по умолчанию, что ломает UTF-8. Всегда использовать [System.IO.File]::ReadAllText/WriteAllText с явным [System.Text.Encoding]::UTF8.

## Universal

- One file = one responsibility
- Always handle errors explicitly (try/catch, fallback UI)
- No magic numbers — use named constants
- Prefer simple over clever
- Never hardcode secrets — always use .env.local
- Before writing code — make sure you understand the task fully
- If task is unclear — ask ONE question before coding

## TypeScript

- `strict: true` in tsconfig.json — no exceptions
- No `any` — use `unknown` if dynamic type needed
- Interfaces for props, types for unions/intersections
- Zod schemas → infer types via `z.infer<typeof schema>`
- Always type function returns explicitly

## React / Next.js

- Functional components only — no class components
- Server Component by default — `'use client'` only when needed
- One component per file
- Props destructuring in function signature
- Early returns for conditional rendering

## HTML / JSX

- Semantic tags first: `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<nav>`
- Accessibility required: `alt` on images, `aria-*` and `role` where needed
- No inline styles — use Tailwind classes

## CSS / Tailwind

- Mobile-first by default: base styles → `sm:` → `md:` → `lg:`
- Use Tailwind utilities — custom CSS only when absolutely needed
- Dark mode support via `dark:` prefix
- Avoid `!important` except for utility overrides

## Error Handling

- Always wrap async operations in try/catch
- User sees: friendly message. Console sees: full error
- Never suppress errors silently

## Design System

- Компоненты — только из @/components/
- Цвета и токены — только через CSS переменные из globals.css
- Стиль — строго по direction.md
- Сайдбар всегда bg-[#1A1F2E] — не менять

## Documentation (MCP Context7)

Before writing code that uses any external library — use MCP Context7 to fetch current documentation first.

Required for:

- `next-auth` / Auth.js v5 — API changed from v4
- `prisma` — transactions, complex queries, typing
- `next` — App Router patterns, Server Components
- `zod` — validation schemas

Rule: Context7 first → then code. Never guess library API from memory.
